dct_title_s: Gaza Strip, October 1986 (Israeli occupied - status to be determined)
dct_description_sm: Map shows built-up areas, civilian and military Israeli-developed areas beyond the 1950 Armistice Line, refugee camps, razed settlements, railroads, and international boundaries. Relief shown by spot heights in meters. UTM and Mercator grids. Includes notes. Central meridian 33°00ʹE. "Israeli-developed area and refugee camp names do not necessarily conform to BGN recommendations." "Boundary representation is not necessarily authoritative." "800812 (E00036) 12-86." South Decimal Degree 31.2167. East Decimal Degree 34.5833. Universal transverse Mercator projection. Relief shown by spot heights. Map shows: "built-up area", Israeli-developed area (civilian) beyond the 1950 Armistice Line, "Israeli-development area (military) beyond the 1950 Armistice Line; Refugee camp; Razed settlement. North Decimal Degree 31.600000. [United States. Central Intelligence Agency]. West Decimal Degree 34.2167.
dct_publisher_sm: [Washington, D.C.] : [Central Intelligence Agency] : [Supt. of Docs., U.S. G.P.O.(distributor)], [1986]
